# NestJS module structure

Use the following layout for each feature module:

```text
src/modules/<name>/
  <name>.module.ts
  <name>.controller.ts
  <name>.service.ts
  <name>.prisma
  dto/
    create-<name>.dto.ts
    update-<name>.dto.ts
    <name>-response.dto.ts
    index.ts
```

## Conventions

- Keep the module folder self-contained: controller, service, dto, and prisma fragment together.
- Export the service in `<name>.module.ts` if other modules consume it.
- Import `QueueModule.register('producer')` only if the module enqueues jobs.
- Use a module-level `index.ts` for outward exports.
- Avoid business logic in modules; that belongs in the service.
